open','','297-revision','','','2013-05-23 18:58:04','2013-05-23 22:58:04','',297,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=298',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (299,1,'2013-05-23 19:00:12','2013-05-23 23:00:12','<p class=\"p1\">More often than we want to admit, the problem is something simple. Make sure the computer’s power cable is plugged in, your keyboard and monitor are plugged in, your power strip or UPS is switched on, and the circuit breaker hasn’t been tripped. If your computer’s battery was completely drained, let it charge for 15 minutes. An old tech support joke ends with the punch line, “Of course I can’t read the manual - there’s a blackout.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">If you have a portable, reset the System Management Controller (see <a title=\"How do I reset the System Management Controller (SMC)?\" href=\"./?p=319\"><em>How do I reset the System Management Controller?</em></a>). If you are sure the power outlet is working, the computer’s power supply or logic board may have died. Bring in the computer for an evaluation.</p>','I press the power button, and nothing happens.','','publish','open','open','','i-press-the-power-button-and-nothing-happens','','','2013-06-18 17:12:07','2013-06-18 21:12:07','',0,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=299',43,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (300,1,'2013-05-23 19:00:05','2013-05-23 23:00:05','<p class=\"p1\">More often than we want to admit, the problem is something simple. Make sure the computer&rsquo;s power cable is plugged in, your keyboard and monitor are plugged in, your power strip or UPS is switched on, and the circuit breaker hasn&rsquo;t been tripped. If your computer&rsquo;s battery was completely drained, let it charge for 15 minutes. An old tech support joke ends with the punch line, &ldquo;Of course I can&rsquo;t read the manual - there&rsquo;s a blackout.&rdquo;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">If you have a portable, reset the System Management Controller (see <em>How do I reset the System Management Controller?&nbsp;</em><span class=\"s1\">below</span>). If you are sure the power outlet is working, the computer&rsquo;s power supply or logic board may have died. Bring in the computer for an evaluation.</p>','I press the power button, and nothing happens.','','inherit','open','open','','299-revision','','','2013-05-23 19:00:05','2013-05-23 23:00:05','',299,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=300',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (301,1,'2013-05-23 19:01:31','2013-05-23 23:01:31','<p class=\"p1\">1. First shut down your Mac. You may need to hold down the Mac’s power button for several seconds to turn it off.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">2. Disconnect all external devices and Ethernet cables (except your mouse, keyboard, and monitor if applicable). If you are using a third-party mouse or keyboard, disconnect those too and plug in your original Apple peripherals if possible.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">3. Now that your external stuff is disconnected, start the Mac and see if the external devices caused the problem. If so, reconnect them one at a time to see when the problem returns.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">4. You can check that your computer is trying to boot from the correct drive. To do so, hold down the Option key immediately after you press the power button to turn your computer on, and then select the drive where your operating system is installed (usually “Macintosh HD”).</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">If these steps don’t resolve your problem, try <a title=\"What is a “Safe Boot” and how do I use it if my Mac isn’t properly starting up?\" href=\"./?p=312\">performing a Safe Boot</a>. If a Safe Boot doesn’t work, try <a title=\"How do I reset the PRAM/NVRAM?\" href=\"./?p=317\">resetting your PRAM/NVRAM</a>. Next, try <a title=\"How do I repair my Mac’s hard drive using Disk Utility?\" href=\"./?p=306\"><em>How do I repair my Mac’s hard drive using Disk Utility?</em></a>. If none of those steps work, bring your computer in to our service department, and we’ll gladly take a look at it for you.</p>','I turn on my computer and it only shows a persistent gray screen, an Apple logo, spinning gear, spinning globe, prohibitory sign, or a folder with a flashing question mark.','','publish','open','open','','i-turn-on-my-computer-and-it-only-shows-a-persistent-gray-screen-an-apple-logo-spinning-gear-spinning-globe-prohibitory-sign-or-a-folder-with-a-flashing-question-mark','','','2013-06-18 17:12:06','2013-06-18 21:12:06','',0,'http://localhost/tekfaqs/?p=301',44,'post','',0);
