" tag=\"osx-apps\" order=\"ASC\" orderby=\"title\"]</div>\n<div class=\"hiddenContent\" id=\"network\">[display-posts posts_per_page=\"-1\" taxonomy=\"os\" tax_term=\"mac-os-x-10-9-mavericks\" tag=\"network\" order=\"ASC\" orderby=\"title\"]</div>\n<div class=\"hiddenContent\" id=\"security\">[display-posts posts_per_page=\"-1\" taxonomy=\"os\" tax_term=\"mac-os-x-10-9-mavericks\" tag=\"security\" order=\"ASC\" orderby=\"title\"]</div>\n<div class=\"hiddenContent\" id=\"repair\">[display-posts posts_per_page=\"-1\" taxonomy=\"os\" tax_term=\"mac-os-x-10-9-mavericks\" tag=\"installation-upgrades-and-repairs\" order=\"ASC\" orderby=\"title\"]</div>\n[/column_one_third]','Mac OS 10.9 (Mavericks)','','inherit','open','open','','688-autosave','','','2013-06-14 14:03:24','2013-06-14 18:03:24','',688,'http://tekserve.wpengine.com/688-autosave/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (692,1,'2013-06-14 15:28:02','2013-06-14 19:28:02','<p class=\"p1\">If you&rsquo;re still using an old PowerBook or iMac, you&rsquo;ve probably run into a problem where you&rsquo;ve wanted to install a new application, or do an update for your web browser or iTunes, and you&rsquo;ve been told you can&rsquo;t because it won&rsquo;t work on your computer. This may well be because your Mac has a PowerPC processor, like an iBook G4 or an iMac G5, and programmers simply aren&rsquo;t writing software that&rsquo;s compatible with them anymore. There is nothing like Rosetta that translates Intel applications to run on PowerPC, and while your computer has had a good, long life, it&rsquo;s time to seriously consider upgrading to a new Intel Mac so that you can take advantage of the new features in OS X, like iCloud integration (<a href=\"http://tekserve.wpengine.com/keywords/icloud/\">see iCloud</a>), and new applications that you can download directly from the Apple App Store.</p>','What do you mean I can\'t run (insert application here) on my old computer?','','publish','open','open','','what-do-you-mean-i-cant-run-insert-application-here-on-my-old-computer','','','2013-06-18 18:00:05','2013-06-18 22:00:05','',0,'http://tekserve.wpengine.com/?p=692',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (693,1,'2013-06-14 15:32:24','2013-06-14 19:32:24','<p class=\"p1\">Not necessarily. It\'s not such a bad idea to have two computers, in case one of them has to come into Tekserve for a repair or upgrade, and you’re going to be without it for a couple of hours or days. Chances are your old computer can still be used to do basic web browsing and emailing to tide you over until you get your other computer back. Just like with your data, it\'s never a bad idea to have a backup. There are also lots of people who have repurposed their old Macs to be file servers, or hooked them up to their TV or stereo to be media centers - so if you feel the urge to tinker around, you\'ll find lots of tutorials online!</p>','If I get a new Mac, does that mean I need to get rid of my old one?','','publish','open','open','','if-i-get-a-new-mac-does-that-mean-i-need-to-get-rid-of-my-old-one','','','2013-06-18 18:00:05','2013-06-18 22:00:05','',0,'http://tekserve.wpengine.com/?p=693',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (694,1,'2013-06-17 10:39:51','2013-06-17 14:39:51','<p class=\"p1\">You have a couple of options, but the most important thing is to make sure that you don&rsquo;t just throw it away in the trash. Unfortunately, there are some chemicals involved in the manufacture of the internal components in your computer that need to be disposed of responsibly. You can bring your old or broken Mac into Tekserve, and we&rsquo;ll not only send it to be recycled, but we can also help you trade it in towards a new computer! You might also want to consider donating it to a family member or a non-profit organization; just because it&rsquo;s not a cutting-edge computer doesn&rsquo;t mean that someone can&rsquo;t use it! More information about e-waste recycling is available on our <a href=\"http://www.tekserve.com/recycling/\">recycling page</a>.</p>','What if I want to get rid of my old or broken computer?','','publish','open','open','','what-if-i-want-to-get-rid-of-my-old-or-broken-computer','','','2013-06-18 18:00:05','2013-06-18 22:00:05','',0,'http://tekserve.wpengine.com/?p=694',0,'post','',0);
